    "title": "Implicit conversion from `fs::path` to `std::string` when constructing file streams",
    "body": "When building with libc++ that has LWG 3430 [implemented](https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/commit/4761e74a276ee1f38596f4849daa9d633929f2ae), constructing `std::ifstream` or `std::ofstream` from an `fs::path` object triggers its implicit conversion to `std::string`. This behavior has been undesirable ever since `fs::path` was introduced. See, for example: https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/a33bd767a37dccf39a094d03c2f62ea81633410f/src/util/fs.h#L54-L55",
